{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":4976,"text":"I am honored to be here,"},{"time":6388,"text":"and I'm honored to talk about this topic,"},{"time":8389,"text":"which I think is of grave importance."},{"time":10238,"text":"We've been talking a lot"},{"time":11485,"text":"about the horrific impacts of plastic\non the planet and on other species,"},{"time":17452,"text":"but plastic hurts people, too --"},{"time":19951,"text":"especially poor people."},{"time":22000,"text":"And both in the production of plastic,"},{"time":25182,"text":"the use of plastic\nand the disposal of plastic,"},{"time":27924,"text":"the people who have\nthe bull's-eye on their foreheads"},{"time":30513,"text":"are poor people."},{"time":32227,"text":"People got very upset"},{"time":35328,"text":"when the BP oil spill happened,"},{"time":38431,"text":"for very good reason."},{"time":39915,"text":"People thought, \"Oh, my God."},{"time":41563,"text":"This is terrible, this oil --\nit's in the water."},{"time":44363,"text":"It's going to destroy\nthe living systems there."},{"time":48305,"text":"People are going to be hurt."},{"time":49763,"text":"This is a terrible thing,"},{"time":51278,"text":"this oil is going to hurt\nthe people in the Gulf.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":53637,"text":"What people don't think about is:"},{"time":55731,"text":"What if the oil had made it\nsafely to shore?"},{"time":58484,"text":"What if the oil actually got\nwhere it was trying to go?"},{"time":61814,"text":"Not only would it have been burned\nin engines and added to global warming,"},{"time":65835,"text":"but there's a place called \"Cancer Alley,\""},{"time":69220,"text":"and the reason it's called \"Cancer Alley\""},{"time":71379,"text":"is because the petrochemical industry"},{"time":74031,"text":"takes that oil and turns it into plastic"},{"time":76211,"text":"and in the process, kills people."},{"time":78914,"text":"It shortens the lives of the people\nwho live there in the Gulf."},{"time":81986,"text":"So oil and petrochemicals are not\njust a problem when there's a spill;"},{"time":85804,"text":"they're a problem when there's not."},{"time":87538,"text":"And what we don't often appreciate"},{"time":89969,"text":"is the price that poor people pay"},{"time":91667,"text":"for us to have these disposable products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94193,"text":"The other thing\nwe often don't appreciate is,"},{"time":96362,"text":"it's not just at the point of production\nthat poor people suffer."},{"time":99486,"text":"Poor people also suffer\nat the point of use."},{"time":102136,"text":"Those of us who earn\na certain income level,"},{"time":104245,"text":"we have something called choice."},{"time":106671,"text":"The reason why you want\nto work hard and have a job"},{"time":109160,"text":"and not be poor and broke"},{"time":110855,"text":"is so you can have choices,\neconomic choices."},{"time":113692,"text":"We actually get a chance\nto choose not to use products"},{"time":117801,"text":"that have dangerous,\npoisonous plastic in them."},{"time":120042,"text":"Other people who are poor\ndon't have those choices."},{"time":122601,"text":"So low-income people often are the ones"},{"time":124599,"text":"who are buying the products that have\nthose dangerous chemicals in them"},{"time":128607,"text":"that their children are using."},{"time":130070,"text":"Those are the people who wind up\ningesting a disproportionate amount"},{"time":133918,"text":"of this poisonous plastic in using it."},{"time":136109,"text":"And people say, \"Well, they should\njust buy a different product.\""},{"time":139366,"text":"Well, the problem with being poor\nis you don't have those choices."},{"time":142525,"text":"You often have to buy\nthe cheapest products."},{"time":144637,"text":"The cheapest products\nare often the most dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147640,"text":"And if that weren't bad enough --"},{"time":149260,"text":"if it wasn't just the production\nof plastic that's giving people cancer"},{"time":152705,"text":"in places like Cancer Alley,"},{"time":154233,"text":"and shortening lives and hurting\npoor kids at the point of use --"},{"time":157765,"text":"at the point of disposal,"},{"time":159872,"text":"once again, it's poor people\nwho bear the burden."},{"time":163502,"text":"Often, we think we're doing a good thing:"},{"time":166131,"text":"You're in your office, drinking\nyour bottled water or whatever it is,"},{"time":169803,"text":"and you think to yourself,\n\"I'm going to throw this away."},{"time":172586,"text":"No -- I'm going to be virtuous.\nI'm going to put it in the blue bin.\""},{"time":176140,"text":"You think, \"I put mine in the blue bin.\""},{"time":178196,"text":"And then you look\nat your colleague and say,"},{"time":181784,"text":"\"Why, you cretin!\nYou put yours in the white bin.\""},{"time":185260,"text":"And we use that as a moral tickle."},{"time":187570,"text":"We feel so good about ourselves."},{"time":189339,"text":"If we -- well, OK, I'm just ... me."},{"time":192618,"text":"Not you, but I feel this way often."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194342,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":196000,"text":"And so we kind of have\nthis moral feel-good moment."},{"time":199320,"text":"But if we were to be able\nto follow that little bottle"},{"time":202716,"text":"on its journey,"},{"time":204205,"text":"we would be shocked\nto discover that, all too often,"},{"time":206794,"text":"that bottle is going to be put on a boat,"},{"time":210049,"text":"it's going to go all the way\nacross the ocean"},{"time":212886,"text":"at some expense,"},{"time":214226,"text":"and it's going to wind up\nin a developing country, often China."},{"time":217769,"text":"I think in our minds, we imagine"},{"time":219381,"text":"somebody's going to take\nthe little bottle and say,"},{"time":221865,"text":"\"Oh, little bottle! We're so happy\nto see you, little bottle.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":225150,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"\"You've served so well.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":229388,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230435,"text":"He's given a little bottle massage,"},{"time":232300,"text":"a little bottle medal."},{"time":234000,"text":"And they say, \"What would\nyou like to do next?\""},{"time":236222,"text":"The little bottle says,\n\"I just don't know ...\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":238594,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":239944,"text":"But that's not actually what happens."},{"time":243090,"text":"You know?"},{"time":244600,"text":"That bottle winds up getting burned."},{"time":249417,"text":"The recycling of plastic\nin many developing countries"},{"time":253063,"text":"means the incineration of the plastic,\nthe burning of the plastic,"},{"time":256237,"text":"which releases incredible toxic chemicals"},{"time":258687,"text":"and, once again, kills people."},{"time":260544,"text":"And so, poor people\nwho are making these products"},{"time":264288,"text":"in petrochemical centers\nlike Cancer Alley,"},{"time":267074,"text":"poor people who are consuming\nthese products disproportionately,"},{"time":270176,"text":"and then poor people who,\neven at the tail end of the recycling,"},{"time":273714,"text":"are having their lives shortened."},{"time":275500,"text":"They're all being harmed -- greatly --"},{"time":279120,"text":"by this addiction that we have\nto disposability."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283984,"text":"Now, you think to yourself --\nI know how you are --"},{"time":286490,"text":"you say, \"That sure is terrible\nfor those poor people."},{"time":291278,"text":"It's just awful. Those poor people."},{"time":294816,"text":"I hope someone does\nsomething to help them.\""},{"time":297602,"text":"But what we don't understand is --"},{"time":300765,"text":"here we are in Los Angeles."},{"time":302590,"text":"We worked very hard\nto get the smog reduction"},{"time":304745,"text":"happening here in Los Angeles."},{"time":306324,"text":"But guess what?"},{"time":307579,"text":"Because they're doing so much\ndirty production in Asia now,"},{"time":310958,"text":"because the environmental laws\ndon't protect the people in Asia now,"},{"time":314590,"text":"almost all of the clean air gains\nand the toxic air gains"},{"time":318656,"text":"that we've achieved here in California"},{"time":320552,"text":"have been wiped out\nby dirty air coming over from Asia."},{"time":324671,"text":"So we all are being hit.\nWe all are being impacted."},{"time":327401,"text":"It's just that the poor people\nget it first and worst."},{"time":330179,"text":"But the dirty production,\nthe burning of toxins,"},{"time":333394,"text":"the lack of environmental\nstandards in Asia,"},{"time":335678,"text":"is actually creating so much\ndirty air pollution,"},{"time":338195,"text":"it's coming across the ocean,"},{"time":339636,"text":"and has erased our gains\nhere in California."},{"time":341774,"text":"We're back where we were in the 1970s."},{"time":343692,"text":"And so we're on one planet,"},{"time":345643,"text":"and we have to be able to get\nto the root of these problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348612,"text":"The root of this problem, in my view,"},{"time":351694,"text":"is the idea of disposability itself."},{"time":354738,"text":"You see, if you understand the link"},{"time":357783,"text":"between what we're doing\nto poison and pollute the planet"},{"time":361535,"text":"and what we're doing to poor people,"},{"time":364000,"text":"you arrive at a very troubling\nbut also very helpful insight:"},{"time":369036,"text":"In order to trash the planet,"},{"time":371308,"text":"you have to trash people."},{"time":373523,"text":"But if you create a world\nwhere you don't trash people,"},{"time":376487,"text":"you can't trash the planet."},{"time":378300,"text":"So now we are at a moment"},{"time":380790,"text":"where the coming together\nof social justice as an idea"},{"time":383662,"text":"and ecology as an idea,"},{"time":386111,"text":"we finally can now see"},{"time":387420,"text":"that they are really,\nat the end of the day, one idea."},{"time":390009,"text":"And it's the idea that we don't have\ndisposable anything."},{"time":393205,"text":"We don't have disposable resources."},{"time":396300,"text":"We don't have disposable species."},{"time":398955,"text":"And we don't have\ndisposable people, either."},{"time":401535,"text":"We don't have a throwaway planet,"},{"time":403581,"text":"and we don't have throwaway\nchildren -- it's all precious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406396,"text":"And as we all begin to come back\nto that basic understanding,"},{"time":409300,"text":"new opportunities for action\nbegin to emerge."},{"time":412895,"text":"Biomimicry,"},{"time":414590,"text":"which is an emerging science,"},{"time":418131,"text":"winds up being a very important\nsocial justice idea."},{"time":421736,"text":"People who are just\nlearning about this stuff:"},{"time":423952,"text":"biomimicry means respecting\nthe wisdom of all species."},{"time":427951,"text":"Democracy, by the way,"},{"time":429139,"text":"means respecting the wisdom\nof all people -- we'll get to that."},{"time":432170,"text":"But biomimicry means\nrespecting the wisdom of all species."},{"time":434980,"text":"It turns out we're a pretty\nclever species."},{"time":437514,"text":"We have this big cortex,\nwe're pretty proud of ourselves."},{"time":440617,"text":"But if we want to make something hard,"},{"time":443204,"text":"we say, \"I know! I'm going\nto make a hard substance."},{"time":445742,"text":"I know! I'm going to get\nvacuums and furnaces"},{"time":449300,"text":"and drag stuff out of the ground"},{"time":451008,"text":"and get things hot\nand poison and pollute ..."},{"time":453921,"text":"But I got this hard thing!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":456804,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457978,"text":"\"I'm so clever!\""},{"time":459601,"text":"And you look behind you,\nand there's destruction all around you."},{"time":462670,"text":"But guess what?"},{"time":463847,"text":"You're so clever,\nbut you're not as clever as a clam."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466704,"text":"A clamshell is hard."},{"time":468458,"text":"There's no vacuums.\nThere's no big furnaces."},{"time":471153,"text":"There's no poison. There's no pollution."},{"time":473117,"text":"It turns out that other species\nfigured out a long time ago"},{"time":477941,"text":"how to create many of the things we need"},{"time":480300,"text":"using biological processes\nthat nature knows how to use well."},{"time":483963,"text":"That insight of biomimicry,\nof our scientists finally realizing"},{"time":487662,"text":"that we have as much\nto learn from other species --"},{"time":490094,"text":"I don't mean taking a mouse\nand sticking it with stuff."},{"time":493300,"text":"I don't mean looking at it from that way,\nabusing the little species."},{"time":496633,"text":"I mean actually respecting them,\nrespecting what they've achieved."},{"time":499913,"text":"That's called biomimicry,"},{"time":501494,"text":"and that opens the door\nto zero waste production;"},{"time":505391,"text":"zero pollution production;"},{"time":507300,"text":"that we could actually enjoy"},{"time":509300,"text":"a high quality of life,\na high standard of living,"},{"time":511945,"text":"without trashing the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513540,"text":"Well, that idea of biomimicry,"},{"time":516604,"text":"respecting the wisdom of all species,"},{"time":518966,"text":"combined with the idea\nof democracy and social justice,"},{"time":522862,"text":"respecting the wisdom\nand the worth of all people,"},{"time":525481,"text":"would give us a different society."},{"time":527300,"text":"We would have a different economy."},{"time":529196,"text":"We would have a green society"},{"time":531530,"text":"that Dr. King would be proud of."},{"time":533959,"text":"That should be the goal."},{"time":535633,"text":"And the way that we get there\nis to first of all recognize"},{"time":538625,"text":"that the idea of disposability"},{"time":541566,"text":"not only hurts the species\nwe've talked about,"},{"time":545700,"text":"but it even corrupts our own society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548475,"text":"We're so proud to live here in California."},{"time":551476,"text":"We just had this vote,\nand everybody's like,"},{"time":553586,"text":"\"Well -- not in our state!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":555348,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":556893,"text":"I don't know what those\nother states were doing, but ...\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":559700,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":561466,"text":"Just so proud."},{"time":564061,"text":"And, yeah, I'm proud, too."},{"time":566436,"text":"But ..."},{"time":569160,"text":"California, though we lead the world\nin some of the green stuff,"},{"time":572700,"text":"we also, unfortunately, lead the world"},{"time":574700,"text":"in some of the gulag stuff."},{"time":577406,"text":"California has one of the highest\nincarceration rates"},{"time":580970,"text":"of all the 50 states."},{"time":582700,"text":"We have a moral challenge\nin this movement."},{"time":585817,"text":"We are passionate about rescuing\nsome dead materials from the landfill,"},{"time":590861,"text":"but sometimes not as passionate"},{"time":592701,"text":"about rescuing living beings,\nliving people."},{"time":595414,"text":"And I would say\nthat we live in a country --"},{"time":598557,"text":"five percent of the world's population,"},{"time":600558,"text":"25 percent of the greenhouse gases,"},{"time":603072,"text":"but also 25 percent\nof the world's prisoners."},{"time":606084,"text":"One of every four people\nlocked up anywhere in the world"},{"time":608768,"text":"is locked up right here\nin the United States."},{"time":610966,"text":"So that is consistent with this idea"},{"time":613700,"text":"that disposability\nis something we believe in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616916,"text":"And yet,"},{"time":619240,"text":"as a movement that has to broaden\nits constituency,"},{"time":623786,"text":"that has to grow,"},{"time":625121,"text":"that has to reach out\nbeyond our natural comfort zone,"},{"time":628247,"text":"one of the challenges\nto the success of this movement,"},{"time":631184,"text":"of getting rid of things like plastic\nand helping the economy shift,"},{"time":634448,"text":"is people look at our movement\nwith some suspicion."},{"time":637864,"text":"And they ask a question,\nand the question is:"},{"time":640484,"text":"How can these people be so passionate?"},{"time":643246,"text":"A poor person, a low-income person,\nsomebody in Cancer Alley,"},{"time":646509,"text":"somebody in Watts,"},{"time":648967,"text":"somebody in Harlem,\nsomebody on an Indian reservation,"},{"time":651700,"text":"might say to themselves --\nand rightfully so --"},{"time":653942,"text":"\"How can these people be so passionate"},{"time":656848,"text":"about making sure"},{"time":658613,"text":"that a plastic bottle\nhas a second chance in life,"},{"time":662700,"text":"or an aluminum can has a second chance,"},{"time":665911,"text":"and yet, when my child gets in trouble\nand goes to prison,"},{"time":669501,"text":"he doesn't get a second chance?\""},{"time":671334,"text":"\"How can this movement\nbe so passionate about saying"},{"time":673840,"text":"we don't have throwaway stuff,\nno throwaway dead materials,"},{"time":676684,"text":"and yet accept throwaway lives"},{"time":679523,"text":"and throwaway communities\nlike Cancer Alley?\""},{"time":681864,"text":"And so, we now get a chance\nto be truly proud of this movement."},{"time":687438,"text":"When we take on topics like this,"},{"time":689149,"text":"it gives us that extra call\nto reach out to other movements"},{"time":693805,"text":"and to become more inclusive and to grow,"},{"time":696171,"text":"and we can finally get out of\nthis crazy dilemma that we've been in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699969,"text":"Most of you are good, softhearted people."},{"time":703389,"text":"When you were younger,\nyou cared about the whole world,"},{"time":706069,"text":"and at some point, somebody said\nyou had to pick an issue,"},{"time":709838,"text":"you had to boil your love\ndown to an issue."},{"time":712282,"text":"\"Can't love the whole world --"},{"time":713829,"text":"you've got to work on trees\nor you've got to work on immigration."},{"time":717447,"text":"You've got to shrink it down\nand be about one issue.\""},{"time":720375,"text":"And really, they fundamentally told you,"},{"time":723319,"text":"\"Are you going to hug a tree?"},{"time":725453,"text":"Or are you going to hug a child? Pick."},{"time":727604,"text":"Are you going to hug a tree?"},{"time":729240,"text":"Or are you going to hug a child? Pick.\""},{"time":731333,"text":"Well, when you start working\non issues like plastic,"},{"time":733809,"text":"you realize the whole thing is connected."},{"time":736032,"text":"And luckily, most of us are blessed\nto have two arms --"},{"time":738836,"text":"we can hug both."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740251,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741644,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}